result.execSummary:
Daniel Paul Johnson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Daniel Paul Johnson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:27 PM CO: SJN, RPR: V. Deiss, Clerk: K. Anderson, Attorney Erica Ellenwood and Intern Ali Casey in court for State of Wisconsin, Attorney Jeremiah James Harrelson in court for Daniel Paul Johnson. Defendant Daniel Paul Johnson appeared by video, in custody. Atty. Harrelson states that he did not have the opportunity to speak with DE. DE states that he chose not speak with public defender. DE sworn. DE confirms address and DOB. Defendant wishes to voluntarily waive extradition to Dakota County, MN. Court finds DE knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily waives right to extradition. Atty. Harrelson makes argument regarding waiver of extradition form. ADA Ellenwood makes argument. Court advises court security to make revision to form to add word allegedly. Defendant executes Waiver and court certifies same. Adjourned: 1:33 PM. kma
Bail/bond hearing scheduled for August 1, 2022 at 01:05 pm.
